The paper deals with the acquisition of gaze direction data from visual information, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a self-reporting mechanism also suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The application of the proposed method to an existing video data set and YouTube videos indicates a potential interest in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of crowdsourcing for data collection aligns with the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
